column5: fished the spring crappie derby on saturday at binbook, weather was great and fishing was even better. i've never seen so many slabs pulled out of there. i believe they had over 15 crappie weighed in over a pound and i was lucky enough to land this slab at 1.82lbs to win it.
Congrets on the PB.  What a beast eh!
Very nice,would that be a white crappie?,not seen much else other than the green type.
Holy cow, that is huge, congrats
Awesome fish! Congrats on the win
you sure thats not a largemouth?....very very nice!!
Amazing, I fished from 6:30 to the last seconds of that tournament and only got 1 1/2 pound crappie! Congrats on the pb!

thanks guys, and davey buoy yes its a white crappie, usually i find the blacks more predominate at binbrook but it was the complete opposite on saturday which was a good thing because the blacks generally don't get as big in there.
Mom A MIA.......that's one big white crappie....
wow !!! thats a huge crappy,man well done !!!
Well done sir!  That is a slab and a half!
Awesome Josh!!!!!!!!!  Slabasaurus Rex!  Nice to see some good fish in that lake.
Wow man, You are on a roll this spring!  Cheers,
Jeebus, thats an awesome crappie!!!  Clarence, you have the best avatar ever....
